reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Attractive and inexpensive
reviews.reviewText: Good quality, looks nice, very functional...fast shipping and was easy to assemble

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The desk wasn't difficult to put together solo and I really like that that it had two choices of layout. There is a ton of leg room and desktop space. The material was much sturdier than I expected. The boards felt like actual wood and not that cheap particle board I'm used to in these desks and the metal added great structure.My only complaints are 1) My PC Tower didn't fit in the shelf designated for it, and 2) The moniter stands are not big enough for my 27" curved moniter. Both of those are probably user error, but still annoying enough to lose a star.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nifty Desk for the price
reviews.reviewText: Box was damaged when received, its kind of heavy so I can see how it got dropped a few time's. They have put edge guards on all the items just for this problem. Only 1 corner was damaged and not bad enough to send it back. All of the attaching bolts and screws come with extra in case you loose or damage one. It went together easy enough, looks nice and is not wobbly. I like it and would buy it again if I needed a light duty desk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great affordable desk !
reviews.reviewText: I was a little skeptical about this desk because of the low price. Took about an hour to put it together and I was thoroughly impressed. All the parts were labeled, instructions were clearly written and in two parts. One for the L on the left and one for the L on the right. I would purchase this again if I ever needed too. No wobble, very stable and plenty of room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I never write reviews but I am just pleased as punch with this desk. Arrived with no damage and took me a little over an hour to “assamble” (misspelling in directions that gave me a giggle). Instructions are clear and there are extra parts, just in case. The desk is sturdy, looks nice, and for the price, this has been an excellent purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars L-O-V-E This Desk
reviews.reviewText: My only complaint is that it’s not a little bigger. But the desk is sturdy, looks nice, easy to build. A fantastic buy. I love it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Ok for the price! Some issues..
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Looks nice when set up but there’s a few issues that aren’t clear when looking at the listing..1) the drawer and filing cabinet are both fabric. There’s a front “wooden” piece, but they’re just flimsy fold out drawers. It is particle board, with a wood finish, and the rest of the drawer is just a few pieces of fabric. The filing cabinet drawer does have metal rods to hold the files BUT they’re both flimsy. The top drawer has rounded edges on the bottom and the bottom has pointed edges, both of which came damaged. It definitely still works, but feels like it diminishes the quality a bit.2) The monitor stands are not actually attached to the desk itself. They’re separate pieces with rubber “grips” to hold them in place. Not ideal for a heavy monitor. I have had my Mac desktop on them and if you try to move the stands with any weight on them, the bottom grippies will rip right off. There are no grips left on the stands as of now.3) the side with the filing cabinet leaves space for a chair BUT the side with the shelves would be very difficult to use as it is too small for legs to fit in a chair. Will use it for a while and see if my opinion changes. *update*: a gaming chair seems to fit fine and I haven’t had any issues with fitting in the desk. Both sides seem to work and I do like sitting at it. I have not raised the legs at all, and have it on the carpet, and it is a good height.I bought it on cyber Monday and the price was reduced so I’m feeling like I got what I paid for, but consider the above issues before buying.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No Swear Desk!
reviews.reviewText: Purchased this desk to serve as a craft desk upstairs in the bedroom after my daughter moved out. I liked the looks of it in the listing as it appeared to have ample flat space. The two monitor stands are not attached but do have silicone feet to prevent movement. As such, you can put them wherever you want. Also, the instructions include setting up the desk two different ways to better suit your space. The instructions were very clear and concise though there were a couple of diagrams that I had to study to make sure holes were pointed in the right direction for upcoming pieces. There are adjustable screw-in feet so the desk can be leveled. It appears to be pretty sturdy.
El escritorio está perfecto a lo esperado, lo armé en la segunda forma ya que así se me acomoda mejor, fácil de armar y materiales de buena calidad para una oficina en casa
